gomodel:SYNGO_5471  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"Pituitary adenylate cyclase-activating polypeptide (PACAP) is a member of the secretin/glucagon/VIP family of peptides.\"\n\nFigure 3: Electron micrographs of rat paraventricular nucleus (PVN) showed PACAP (gene ADCYAP1) localized to presynaptic terminals, where staining is observed in some large dense code vesicles.. Experimental description: \"Adult, male Sprague-Dawley rats were used for this study\"" ;
